Name: ARR (from most recent deal)
Description:
The annual recurring revenue (ARR) is the active deal‚Äôs annual revenue. It is calculated based on the term length and values of the recurring line items associated with the deal. If there‚Äôs no term length, HubSpot assumes a term of 12 months.

This synchronizing property retrieves the Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) value from the deal associated with this leader, identified as ‚ÄúActive.‚Äù HubSpot automatically calculates this value based on the line items included in the deal.
Usages: Dataset (1); Sales view (4); Data highlights card (1); Properties v3 card (1)

Name: Auto-Renewal (from most recent deal)
Description:
Auto-renewal indicates whether a deal will automatically renew at the end of its term without requiring manual intervention or re-signing. This information reflects the last contracted terms.

This synchronizing property retrieves the auto-renewal value from the deal associated with this leader, labeled as ‚ÄúActive.‚Äù The AE manually set this value when closing the most recent deal with the leader.
Usages: Dataset (1); Sales view (4); Properties v3 card (1)

Name: MRR (from most recent deal)
Description:
The monthly recurring revenue (MRR) is the recurring revenue for this leader each month.
